INSERT INTO `reversion_version` VALUES (1,'1','json','[{\"model\": \"Group.grouparticles\", \"pk\": 1, \"fields\": {\"article\": 1, \"user\": 7, \"group\": 1}}]','GroupArticles object',21,1,'default'),(2,'1','json','[{\"model\": \"BasicArticle.articles\", \"pk\": 1, \"fields\": {\"title\": \"Writeup\", \"body\": \"<h3><strong>Inappropriate Content Handling</strong></h3><p>To implement this, I would take the text of the article when the user tries to publish it and feed it to a machine learning model. The model would be trained on an existing database in the backend which would probably give a confidence score on how appropriate the content is. Two cases might arise: one, where the model predicts the article to be inappropriate, but the user insists it to be appropriate, the user will submit it for a review by a moderator; and second, where the model predicted the article was appropriate, but it wasn\\u2019t. In the second case, there would be a button to report such articles. If a sufficient number of users reported the article, then it will be reviewed by a moderator. In case, the moderator decides the article to be indeed inappropriate, the article will be removed, and the model will be tuned accordingly.</p><h3><strong>Recommendation System</strong></h3><p>The recommendation system will suggest users new articles depending on which articles he/she has liked or viewed previously. Communities will be suggested in a similar way. The suggestions could appear on his dashboard, or maybe on the homepage. If the user is new, the most popular articles or communities could be suggested.</p><h3><strong>Event Logs</strong></h3><p>In case, recommendation system uses users view history to suggest new articles or communities, the event logs will be generated when a user views a community or an article. These event logs will be used to create a view history for every user which will help in training the recommendation system.</p>\", \"image\": \"\", \"created_at\": \"2018-02-07T